How are ratings calculated?
To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

View Image Gallery
Amazon Customer
3.0 out of 5 stars Deleted review.
Reviewed in India on 24 May 2023
My initial review got deleted because I have this backpack an average rating lol. So there's another one. The build quality on this backpack is average. The straps are bulky and there are loose threads which sums up its mediocre quality. I've compared it with two of the other backpacks that i own under the same price bracket of ₹2000. Imo the NBA backpack from Decathlon looks the best, but there's no separate laptop section since it's a basketball backpack. The uppercase backpack has more pockets and has a water repellent coating but a backpack's build quality and finishing is more important to me than the mentioned two pros of this backpack, so the NBA backpack is clearly a better pick for me. Now comparing the uppercase backpack to my Mi backpack in blue, it really stands no chance against it. Everything on my Mi backpack is miles better than this cheap feeling backpack; be it the build quality, finishing, the materials, the number of pockets/sections, water repellency, everything. Unfortunately the Mi backpack isn't available anymore. So I'd suggest either going with the NBA backpack or search for sales on Adidas/Puma backpacks. Basically I'm suggesting that this backpack is mediocre and there will probably still be better options for the same price.

5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect bag with ample space for regular everyday use
Reviewed in India 🇮🇳 on 6 June 2023
Colour: BlackVerified Purchase
The bag looks really good, and for a couple of days everyone who noticed the bag asked where I got it. It isn't the most spacious, so if you carry a lot of stuff to your office or college, perhaps this isn't the right bag for you. However, for a 15-inch laptop, charger, headphones and a couple of books, this is more than spacious enough. The flap on the top has a pocket that can be used to store small stuff like pens. All in all, if you don't like to carry around everything you own, this is an amazing bag.
